<p>What is the length of the unmeasured side of the triangle? <fillin characters="20" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>7.95</li></ul></p><p>Because it does not matter which leg is a and which is b we call the missing leg x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}+{5.10}^{{2}}={9.45}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}+{26.01}={89.3025}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}={89.3025}-{26.01}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}={63.2925}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{x}^{{2}}}}=\sqrt{{{63.2925}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx{7.95}</m>.</p>
</solution>
